@AustralianPostCode.description: A four digit numeric descriptor for a postal delivery area, aligned with placename, suburb or locality and in some circumstances a unique Postal Delivery Type.
@AustralianPostCode.label: Australian Post Code

@AustralianState.description: The defined State or Territory in Australia (in abbreviated format) that the specific placename/address is located.
@AustralianState.label: Australian State

@Country.description: The destination country of the address
@Country.label: Country

@DataSource.description: The source of data used in searching information about an address.
@DataSource.label: Data Source

@GNAF_ID.description: Geocoded National Address File. A G-NAF ID is a unique combination of address detail used to identify each property in Australia
@GNAF_ID.label: GNAF_ID

@LGAName.description: A local government area (LGA) is an administrative division of a country that a local government is responsible for. The size of an LGA varies by country but it is generally a subdivision of a state, province, division, or territory.
@LGAName.label: LGA Name

@Latitude.description: Latitude is a geographic coordinate that specifies the north-south position of a point on the Earth's surface
@Latitude.label: Latitude

@Longitude.description: Longitude is a geographic coordinate that specifies the east-west position of a point on the Earth's surface
@Longitude.label: Longitude

@OverseasPostCode.description: A series of letters and/or digits for a postal delivery area overseas.
@OverseasPostCode.label: Overseas Post Code

@OverseasState.description: The State, Province or Territory overseas that the specific placename/address is located.
@OverseasState.label: Overseas State

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this address within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@Suburb.description: The full name of the placename or Post Office of delivery containing the specific address, which may include a Delivery Centre or a Business Centre.
@Suburb.label: Suburb

@TBAAddress.description: For Pre-Approval loans, the address of the property is not required.
@TBAAddress.label: TBA Address

@Type.description: Determines if the address is Standard, Non Standard, a DX Box or a PO BOX
@Type.label: Type

@UniqueID.description: Unique identification assigned to this address.
@UniqueID.label: Unique ID

@Exchange.description: An exchange box in an authorised DX system
@Exchange.label: Exchange

@Number.description: An identification number, used for tracking the documents from the moment they're collected to the time they arrive at their destination.
@Number.label: Number

@Provider.description: The name of the company providing DX mailing services
@Provider.label: Provider

DeliveryPoint.description: Details for assisting in more accurately locating and making deliveries to the address.
DeliveryPoint.label: Delivery Point

@Identifier.description: Uniquely identifies every delivery point in the Postal Address File (PAF) or equivalent in other countries.
@Identifier.label: Identifier

@IdentifierBarcode.description: The barcode encoded version of the Delivery Point Identifier.
@IdentifierBarcode.label: Identifier Barcode

@Exchange.description: An exchange box in an authorised PO system
@Exchange.label: Exchange

@Number.description: An identification number, forming part of an address, for the channel of postal delivery.
@Number.label: Number

@Type.description: The specification of the identification of a postal delivery service such as General Post Office Box, Community Mail Bag, etc. to clearly distinguish it from another when applicable.
@Type.label: Type

@BuildingName.description: The full name used to identify the physical building or property. Usually this information is not abbreviated. Should include any reference to a wing or other components of a building complex, if applicable.
@BuildingName.label: Building Name

@Level.description: Descriptors used to identify the floor or level of a multi-storey building or complex.
@Level.label: Level

@LevelType.description: The building level type of a standard address.
@LevelType.label: Level Type

@LotSection.description: The lot or section number of the property. Usually only used until a street number is assigned.
@LotSection.label: Lot Section

@StreetName.description: The full street name used to identify the street location of the property.
@StreetName.label: Street Name

@StreetNumber.description: To record the numeric or numeric/alpha reference number of a house or property.
@StreetNumber.label: Street Number

@StreetSuffix.description: A suffix used to further describe the part of the address that offers directional information. For addresses in New Zealand, this attribute is used for the field referred to as street direction.
@StreetSuffix.label: Street Suffix

@StreetType.description: Used to identify the thoroughfare type
@StreetType.label: Street Type

@ToStreetNumber.description: The upper bound of a range given for the street number of a house or property.
@ToStreetNumber.label: To Street Number

@ToUnitNumber.description: The upper bound of a range given for the unit number of a house or property.
@ToUnitNumber.label: To Unit Number

@Unit.description: The specification of the type of a separately identifiable portion within a building complex or marina with its associated number or identifier to clearly distinguish it from another. Can either be depicted by numerals or alpha characters, or a mixture of both.
@Unit.label: Unit

Ex-Serving.description: ADF member who served in the Permanent or Reserve Services, but who subsequently separated.
Ex-Serving.label: Ex-Serving

Permanent.description: ADF member currently serving in a regular capacity and still serving in a permanent regular capacity.
Permanent.label: Permanent

Reserve.description: ADF member in the active or inactive reserve forces.
Reserve.label: Reserve

applicantCurrentStateTypeList.description: a predefined list of statuses representing an applicant's current state, including their life status, physical condition, and legal capacity.

Deceased.description: The applicant has passed away, particularly identified during the discharge process.
Deceased.label: Deceased

Legally Disabled.description: The applicant has a legally recognized mental impairment that significantly limits major life activities and may impact their ability to make financial or legal decisions.
Legally Disabled.label: Legally Disabled

Physically Disabled.description: The applicant has a legally recognized physical impairment that significantly limits major life activities.
Physically Disabled.label: Physically Disabled

Sound.description: The applicant is an active borrower who is alive. This status is specifically checked during the discharge process to account for any changes in the applicant's life status.
Sound.label: Sound

Borrower.description: The party is applying in the capacity of a borrower on the loan.
Borrower.label: Borrower

Borrower and Guarantor.description: The party is applying in the capacity of both borrower and guarantor on the loan.
Borrower and Guarantor.label: Borrower and Guarantor

Guarantor.description: The party is applying in the capacity of a guarantor on the loan.
Guarantor.label: Guarantor

Alt Doc.description: Indicates that the applicants will provide alternative/non-traditional documentation in support of their financial position.
Alt Doc.label: Alt Doc

Full Doc.description: Indicates that the applicants will provide documentary evidence in support of their financial position, including income.
Full Doc.label: Full Doc

Lo Doc.description: Indicates that the applicants will provide limited documentation in support of their financial position, but will instead typically provide a declaration as to financial position in particular income.
Lo Doc.label: Lo Doc

No Doc.description: Indicates that the applicants will not provide documentary evidence in support of their financial position. Also known as an asset lend.
No Doc.label: No Doc

Deposit Account.description: The application is for a deposit account.
Deposit Account.label: Deposit Account

Facility Drawdown.description: The application is for a loan within an existing approved umbrella master facility.

Lease.description: Application is for a finance or operating lease.
Lease.label: Lease

Loan.description: Application is for a standard loan facility.
Loan.label: Loan

Loan Variation.description: The application is to vary one or more existing loan accounts.
Loan Variation.label: Loan Variation

Overdraft.description: Loan application is for an overdraft or similar non-amortising loan facility.
Overdraft.label: Overdraft

Prequalification.description: Loan application is for prequalification of applicants, usually prior to identification of the security property to be purchased using the loan funds.
Prequalification.label: Prequalification

Unsecured.description: Loan application is for an unsecured loan facility.
Unsecured.label: Unsecured

businessStructureExcludingTrustList.description: A list of the types of business structure for an enterprise, excluding trusts.

Company.description: A company is a separate legal entity, unlike a sole trader or a partnership structure. This means the company has the same rights as a natural person and can incur debt, sue and be sued. The company's owners (the shareholders) can limit their personal liability and are generally not liable for company debts.
Company.label: Company

Partnership.description: A partnership is a type of business structure that involves a number of entities who carry on a business together.
Partnership.label: Partnership

Sole Trader.description: A sole trader business structure is a person trading as the individual legally responsible for all aspects of the business.
Sole Trader.label: Sole Trader

Loan Funded by Lender.label: Loan Funded by Lender

Payout Figure Received.description: The total amount required to pay out the loan has been received.
Payout Figure Received.label: Payout Figure Received

Payout Figure Rejected.description: The total amount required to pay out the loan has been rejected.
Payout Figure Rejected.label: Payout Figure Rejected

PreApproved.description: Application conditionally approved subject to final identification of security property.
PreApproved.label: PreApproved

Progress Payment Complete.description: A progress payment has been completed.
Progress Payment Complete.label: Progress Payment Complete

Progress Payment Message.description: A message about the Progress Payment process.
Progress Payment Message.label: Progress Payment Message

Ready for Progress Payment.description: The application is in a state in which it is ready to begin the Progress Payment process.
Ready for Progress Payment.label: Ready for Progress Payment

Ready for Settlement.description: The application is in a state in which it is ready to begin the Settlement process.
Ready for Settlement.label: Ready for Settlement

Referred for Credit Assessment.description: Application has been referred for manual credit assessment.
Referred for Credit Assessment.label: Referred for Credit Assessment

Referred to Broker.description: Application has been referred to the Broker.
Referred to Broker.label: Referred to Broker

Referred to Mortgage Insurer.description: Application has been referred to the Mortgage Insurer.
Referred to Mortgage Insurer.label: Referred to Mortgage Insurer

Reverted for Rework.description: The application requires further rework and re-decision by the lender.
Reverted for Rework.label: Reverted for Rework

Reverted to Capture.description: Application has been reverted to the data capture stage to update or correct data.
Reverted to Capture.label: Reverted to Capture

Security Documents Sent to Custodian.description: The security documents have been sent to the custodian.
Security Documents Sent to Custodian.label: Security Documents Sent to Custodian

Security Documents Sent to Lender.description: The security documents have been sent to the lender.
Security Documents Sent to Lender.label: Security Documents Sent to Lender

Security Packet Received.description: The security packet has been received.
Security Packet Received.label: Security Packet Received

Security Registered.description: The security has been registered with the Land Titles Office
Security Registered.label: Security Registered

Service Coordinator Assigned.description: A service coordinator has been assigned to process the application.
Service Coordinator Assigned.label: Service Coordinator Assigned

Settlement Cancelled.description: The settlement process has been cancelled.
Settlement Cancelled.label: Settlement Cancelled

Settlement Completed.description: Application has gone to settlement; may or may not have been fully drawn down; accounts may have had a new identifier allocated to them by the Lender (known as Post Settlement Application Number or Facility identifier).
Settlement Completed.label: Settlement Completed

Settlement Date Booked.description: The settlement date has been booked.
Settlement Date Booked.label: Settlement Date Booked

Settlement Date Confirmed.description: The settlement date has been confirmed by all parties.
Settlement Date Confirmed.label: Settlement Date Confirmed

Settlement Date Estimated.description: The estimated settlement date, which is 21 days or as long as six weeks post the exchange of contracts.
Settlement Date Estimated.label: Settlement Date Estimated

Settlement Delayed.description: The settlement process has been delayed.
Settlement Delayed.label: Settlement Delayed

Settlement Funds Received.description: The funds required at settlement have been received.
Settlement Funds Received.label: Settlement Funds Received

Settlement Rebooked.description: The settlement date has been rebooked.
Settlement Rebooked.label: Settlement Rebooked

Solicitor Instructed.description: The solicitors conducting the property transaction have been instructed.
Solicitor Instructed.label: Solicitor Instructed

Solicitor Instruction Received.description: The instruction for the solicitors conducting the property transaction have been received.
Solicitor Instruction Received.label: Solicitor Instruction Received

Supporting Documents Determined to Be In.description: The supporting documents provided by the customer do not cover the checklist requirements, additional supporting documents are expected.
Supporting Documents Determined to Be In.label: Supporting Documents Determined to Be Incomplete

Supporting Documents Have Been Verified.description: The customer provided supporting documents have been verified.
Supporting Documents Have Been Verified.label: Supporting Documents Have Been Verified

Supporting Documents Received.description: The customer provided supporting documentation have been received.
Supporting Documents Received.label: Supporting Documents Received

Title Search Ordered.description: A property title search has been ordered.
Title Search Ordered.label: Title Search Ordered

Title Search Received.description: The results of the property title search have been received.
Title Search Received.label: Title Search Received

Unconditionally Approved.description: All conditions to conditional approval have been met and Application has received formal/final approval.
Unconditionally Approved.label: Unconditionally Approved

Valuation Approved.description: The property valuation has been approved.
Valuation Approved.label: Valuation Approved

Valuation Cancelled.description: The property valuation ordered has been cancelled.
Valuation Cancelled.label: Valuation Cancelled

Valuation Not Required.description: A property valuation is not required.
Valuation Not Required.label: Valuation Not Required

Valuation Ordered.description: The property valuation has been ordered.
Valuation Ordered.label: Valuation Ordered

Valuation Received.description: A completed property valuation has been received from the Valuation Firm.
Valuation Received.label: Valuation Received

Variation Initialised.description: A Variation to the borrower's facility has been initiated.
Variation Initialised.label: Variation Initialised

Withdrawn.description: Application has been stopped at client's initiative.
Withdrawn.label: Withdrawn

Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property

Acceptance Fee.description: A fee charged by the bank for taking the legal obligation of paying a commercial bill on its maturity date. Generally used when taking over a commercial bill.
Acceptance Fee.label: Acceptance Fee

Additional Security Fee.description: Fee is charged for adding one or more additional securities after loan settlement.
Additional Security Fee.label: Additional Security Fee

Administrative Fee.description: Fee charged by the bank if a customer repays their loan in full before the fixed rate period expires, or makes partial prepayments exceeding a set limit per year during the fixed rate period.
Administrative Fee.label: Administrative Fee

Annual Fee.description: Fee is charged for administration and maintenance of credit facilities, usually for revolving credit loans or credit cards.
Annual Fee.label: Annual Fee

Application Fee.description: Fee is charged for processing and assessment of the application for the loan.
Application Fee.label: Application Fee

Brokerage Fee.description: Fee is charged when a broker has assisted borrowers in finding and obtaining approval for a loan. This fee may be charged to the buyer, seller or both.
Brokerage Fee.label: Brokerage Fee

Cancelled Cheque Fee.description: Fee for cancelling cheques prepared for settlement.
Cancelled Cheque Fee.label: Cancelled Cheque Fee

Cash Benefit Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Cash Benefit Insurance. Cash benefit insurance is related to personal loan products (in particular car loans), and covers the owner if their car is written off/destroyed for any costs of replacing the vehicle (above and beyond the payout they would receive from full comprehensive coverage).
Cash Benefit Insurance.label: Cash Benefit Insurance

Construction Progress Inspection Fee.description: Fee is charged each time a property valuer inspects building works during the course of a property being built in order to ensure that building is in accordance with the plans and expectations.
Construction Progress Inspection Fee.label: Construction Progress Inspection Fee

Consumer Credit Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Consumer Credit Insurance (CCI). CCI is an optional insurance policy that protects borrowers against changes in circumstances that negatively affect their ability to pay back the loan such as death, injury or illness and involuntary unemployment. The premium can generally be added to the loan as a lump sum or can be paid monthly.
Consumer Credit Insurance.label: Consumer Credit Insurance

Deferred Establishment Fee.description: Fee charged when a loan is paid off before a set period has elapsed.
Deferred Establishment Fee.label: Deferred Establishment Fee

Documentation Fee.description: Fee is charged for preparation of loan documents. The amount varies based on the complexity of the loan application.
Documentation Fee.label: Documentation Fee

Early Repayment Admin Fee.description: Fee charged when customer repays the loan earlier than the end of the loan term.
Early Repayment Admin Fee.label: Early Repayment Admin Fee

Early Termination Adjustment Fee.description: Fee payable on fixed rate loans where prepayment amount and specials paid this fixed rate year on the loan is greater than specials repay limit.
Early Termination Adjustment Fee.label: Early Termination Adjustment Fee

Establishment Fee.description: Fee is charged for the establishment of the loan facility. For some financial institutions, this is a general term used for fees that one may incur for the bank to set up a loan which may include Application Fee, Settlement Fee, etc. For some financial institutions, this is the same as an Application Fee.
Establishment Fee.label: Establishment Fee

Excess Cheque Fee.description: Fee for each bank cheque in excess of the allowance.
Excess Cheque Fee.label: Excess Cheque Fee

Extended Warranty Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Extended Warranty Insurance. This insurance (also called mechanical breakdown insurance or motor breakdown insurance (MBI)) commences after your new car warranty ends and provides some cover for the repair or replacement of specific parts.
Extended Warranty Insurance.label: Extended Warranty Insurance

Guarantee Asset Protection Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Guaranteed Asset Protection (GAP) Insurance. GAP insurance (also called motor equity insurance or shortfall insurance) covers the lender for the difference between what a borrower owes on the car loan, and what the car is insured for under comprehensive car insurance, if the car is written off.
Guarantee Asset Protection Insurance.label: Guarantee Asset Protection Insurance

Inspection Fee.description: A fee charged for the inspection of an asset. An inspection usually occurs to confirm the location of the asset, determine the condition of the asset, and confirm the asset documents match with the physical asset.
Inspection Fee.label: Inspection Fee

LMI.description: Premium charged for taking out Lenders Mortgage Insurance. Lenders Mortgage Insurance is charged by home loan lenders, typically required when the amount to be borrowed is more than 80% of the value of the property. It is either a one-off payment at the time of settlement or can be added to the monthly loan repayments.
LMI.label: LMI

Land Titles Office Final Search Fee.description: Fee is charged when a final search of the title is ordered to ensure that the property is clear from any interest or restrictions that may have been recorded prior to settlement.
Land Titles Office Final Search Fee.label: Land Titles Office Final Search Fee
Land Titles Office Final Search Fee.path: feeTypeList.Land Titles Office Final Search Fee

Land Titles Office Search Fee.description: Fee is charged when title search is ordered to ascertain the ownership of a property and determine whether there are existing encumbrances, covenants or easements that may be recorded on the title.
Land Titles Office Search Fee.label: Land Titles Office Search Fee

Legal Fee.description: Fee is charged to cover legal fees incurred by the lender in arranging the loan.
Legal Fee.label: Legal Fee

Line Fee.description: A fee charged by the bank to keep the credit available for the applicants to use, whether it is a commercial loan, term loan or a credit facility.
Line Fee.label: Line Fee

Loan Fee.description: Fee is charged for the on-going cost of administration and servicing for the loan. Usually on a monthly basis.
Loan Fee.label: Loan Fee

Loan Split Fee.description: Fee charged when a borrower requests to divide their loan into multiple split loans or portions, such as fixed and variable interest rate components.
Loan Split Fee.label: Loan Split Fee

Mortgage Registration.description: Fee is charged by the Title Office to register the lender's mortgage on the title for a security.
Mortgage Registration.label: Mortgage Registration

Motor Vehicle Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out motor vehicle insurance. Motor vehicle insurance is a type of insurance that provides financial protection against physical damage or bodily injury resulting from traffic collisions and against liability that could also arise from incidents in a vehicle.
Motor Vehicle Insurance.label: Motor Vehicle Insurance

Other.description: Fee charged is not described by one of the enumerated values in the list.
Other.label: Other

PPSR Fee.description: A fee associated with registering a non-real estate asset on the Personal Property Securities Register (PPSR) when it is used as security on a loan.
PPSR Fee.label: PPSR Fee

Package Fee.description: A fee charged for packaging a number of products together.
Package Fee.label: Package Fee

Rate Lock Fee.description: A fee charged for fixing an interest rate prior to the advancement of funds under the credit facility.
Rate Lock Fee.label: Rate Lock Fee

Re-documentation Fee.description: Fee is charged when documents such as Loan Agreement or Variation Contract are re-issued prior to settlement due to change requested by either customer or introducer.
Re-documentation Fee.label: Re-documentation Fee

Reduced Equity Fee.description: An alternative name for risk fee.
Reduced Equity Fee.label: Reduced Equity Fee

Risk Fee.description: A fee charged to offset the risk of a high LVR, instead of paying LMI.
Risk Fee.label: Risk Fee

Rollover Fee.description: A fee charged when rolling over a commercial bill.
Rollover Fee.label: Rollover Fee

Security Guarantee Fee.description: A fee charged for each security guarantee associated with the credit facility.
Security Guarantee Fee.label: Security Guarantee Fee

Security Processing Fee.description: A one-time fee charged by a lender for verifying, registering, and handling legal and administrative tasks related to a loan's security, such as title searches and mortgage registration.
Security Processing Fee.label: Security Processing Fee

Security Release Fee.description: Fee is charged when a lender removes their legal charge from the security held against a mortgage or loan. This is sometimes called Discharge Fee.
Security Release Fee.label: Security Release Fee

Service Plan.description: A fee associated with an ongoing plan to service the asset.
Service Plan.label: Service Plan

Settlement Fee.description: Fee is charged when borrowers finish paying off the balance on a loan, or refinance with another lender. Also known as Termination Fee or Discharge Fee or Early-exit Fee.
Settlement Fee.label: Settlement Fee

Solicitor Fees.description: A fee charged by solicitor or conveyancer for handling legal aspects of the property purchase
Solicitor Fees.label: Solicitor Fees

Stamp Duty on Mortgage.description: Fee paid to the State Revenue Office for stamping of mortgage or other security documents.
Stamp Duty on Mortgage.label: Stamp Duty on Mortgage

Stamp Duty on Mortgage Discharge.description: The stamp duty payable for the discharge of a mortgage.
Stamp Duty on Mortgage Discharge.label: Stamp Duty on Mortgage Discharge

Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property.description: Fee paid to the State Revenue Office for stamping of transfer or other assignments of ownership document.
Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property.label: Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property
Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property.path: feeTypeList.Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property

Substitute Security Fee.description: Fee is charged when the current property security of a loan is substituted for another property. This usually occurs when the borrower intends to sell the existing property security.
Substitute Security Fee.label: Substitute Security Fee

Switch Fee.description: Fee is charged when all or part of an existing loan balance will be converted to another product, another type of interest rate (change between fixed and variable) or repayment type (change between interest only payments and principal and interest payments).
Switch Fee.label: Switch Fee

Third Party Document Production Fee.description: Fee is charged when producing a Certificate of Title or other security documents.
Third Party Document Production Fee.label: Third Party Document Production Fee

Title Transfer Fee.description: Fee is charged when there is a transfer of ownership; for example property title transfer or vehicle registration transfer.
Title Transfer Fee.label: Title Transfer Fee

Top Up Establishment Fee.description: Fee charged for the establishment of the top-up loan facility. For some financial institutions, this is a general term used for fees that one may incur for the bank to set up a loan which may include Application Fee, Settlement Fee, etc.
Top Up Establishment Fee.label: Top Up Establishment Fee

Tyre and Rim Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Tyre and Rim Insurance. This insurance covers the damage to the tyres and rims outside of an accident. This covers tyres, rims, towing costs, car rentals or accommodation costs.
Tyre and Rim Insurance.label: Tyre and Rim Insurance

Unused Facility Fee.description: A fee charged when a customer has unused limit on their facility. Applies to commercial bills only.
Unused Facility Fee.label: Unused Facility Fee

Valuation Fee.description: A fee charged for the assessment of the value of the security.
Valuation Fee.label: Valuation Fee

Withdrawal of Caveat Fee.description: Fee is charged when caveat will be withdrawn/removed and lodged to the corresponding land or property information office.
Withdrawal of Caveat Fee.label: Withdrawal of Caveat Fee

Withdrawal of Writ Fee.description: Fee is charged for the removal of a writ recorded against a title.
Withdrawal of Writ Fee.label: Withdrawal of Writ Fee

Parenting Payment.description: Parenting Payment is government provided income support for parents or guardians to help with the cost of raising children.

Service Pension.description: Service pension is a service pension/income support payment that provides a regular income to veterans and their partners.

Joint Tenants.description: The parties specified as the owners of the property hold their interest as joint tenants.

Joint Tenants Inter Se.description: The parties specified as the owners of the property hold their interest as joint tenants with the right of survivorship.

Other.description: The parties specified as the owners of the property hold an interest which is not specified on the holding list.

Pastoral Lease.description: The parties specified as the owners of the property hold their interest as lessees, granting them the right to use designated land for pastoral activities, primarily grazing livestock.

Sole.description: The party specified as the owner of the property holds their interest as sole proprietor.

Tennant Common in Equal Shares.description: The parties specified as the owners of the property hold their interest as tenants in common in equal shares.

Tennant Common in Shares of.description: The parties specified as the owners of the property hold their interest as tenants in common in unspecified shares.
Tennant Common in Shares of.label: Tennant Common in Shares of

Time Share.description: The parties specified as the owners of the property hold their interest under a time share arrangement.

Trustee.description: The parties specified as the owners of the property hold their interest as a trustee.

Amortising Home Loan.description: Liability is an amortising home loan. A loan that requires the borrower to make scheduled, periodic payments that are applied to both the principal and interest.
Amortising Home Loan.label: Amortising Home Loan

Bridging Finance.description: Liability is a bridging loan. A short term loan designed to allow a borrower to finance the purchase of a new property before selling an existing property. An assessment for a bridging loan involves calculation of peak debt and end debt.
Bridging Finance.label: Bridging Finance

Buy Now Pay Later.description: The liability is a buy now pay later facility according to the lender's policy.
Buy Now Pay Later.label: Buy Now Pay Later

Chattel Mortgage.description: Liability is a chattel mortgage. A finance company lends money to the customer to purchase movable equipment (the 'chattel'), in return for regular repayments. The customer takes ownership upon purchase, and an ASIC-registered Charge provides loan security.
Chattel Mortgage.label: Chattel Mortgage

Commercial Bill.description: Liability is a commercial bill, typically associated with business lending or high-end investment lending
Commercial Bill.label: Commercial Bill

Commercial Hire Purchase.description: Liability is a commercial hire purchase. The lessor secures and pays for an asset on the lessee's behalf with an offer to hire it back to the lessee for an agreed term. The lessor retains ownership of the asset until the lessee pays it off on a principal plus interest basis.
Commercial Hire Purchase.label: Commercial Hire Purchase

Contingent Liability.description: Liability is has not yet crystallised but may arise in future on the happening of certain events or contingencies
Contingent Liability.label: Contingent Liability

Finance Lease.description: Liability is a finance lease. An arrangement where a finance company purchases an asset, and use of the asset is granted to the customer through a series of payments until the end of term, when the customer can acquire ownership by paying the residual value.
Finance Lease.label: Finance Lease

Government Benefits Debt.description: Liability is a debt owed to the government.
Government Benefits Debt.label: Government Benefits Debt

HECS-HELP.description: Liability is a debt under the Commonwealth Higher Education Contribution Scheme
HECS-HELP.label: HECS-HELP

Hire Purchase.description: Liability is owed under a hire purchase agreement
Hire Purchase.label: Hire Purchase

Invoice Financing Loan.description: An invoice financing loan secured by one or more outstanding sales invoices owed to the borrower.
Invoice Financing Loan.label: Invoice Financing Loan

Lease.description: Liability is owed under a finance lease, including for a motor vehicle or equipment
Lease.label: Lease

Line of Credit.description: Liability has a limit up to which the borrower may draw, but which has no regular principal repayment obligations; as opposed to a Term Loan
Line of Credit.label: Line of Credit

Line of Credit Home Loan.description: Liability is a line of credit home loan. A revolving credit facility for a product that is secured by a residential property.
Line of Credit Home Loan.label: Line of Credit Home Loan

Loan as Guarantor.description: Liability is the contingent liability of a guarantor for guaranteed obligations of a third party to a lender
Loan as Guarantor.label: Loan as Guarantor

Margin Loan.description: Liability which lets you borrow money to invest and uses your shares or managed funds as security.
Margin Loan.label: Margin Loan

Mortgage Loan.description: DEPRECATED and to be deleted in a breaking release on or after May 1 2017. Liability is a loan secured by real property
Mortgage Loan.label: Mortgage Loan

Operating Lease.description: Liability is an operating lease. An agreement where an asset's owner permits its use by the customer for a term that is less than the useful or economic life of the asset in return for regular payments. Ownership rights are not transferred and the customer can return the equipment to the owner at the end of term without further obligation.
Operating Lease.label: Operating Lease

Other.description: Liability is not described by one of the other enumerated values in the list
Other.label: Other

Other Loan.description: Liability is loan that is not described by the loan types Mortgage Loan, Personal Loan, Term Loan
Other Loan.label: Other Loan

Outstanding Taxation.description: Liability is a debt owed to a public authority for unpaid taxes, including BAS and PAYGW
Outstanding Taxation.label: Outstanding Taxation

Overdraft.description: Liability is a credit buffer on a deposit account, unsecured, or an extra buffer above the approved limit of a credit facility
Overdraft.label: Overdraft

Personal Loan.description: Liability is a personal loan, typically unsecured and for personal purposes such as funding travel or the purchase of a car
Personal Loan.label: Personal Loan

Term Loan.description: Liability is a loan that has a term, as opposed to a Line Of Credit
Term Loan.label: Term Loan

Trade Finance Loan.description: A trade finance loan for financing domestic and international trade.
Trade Finance Loan.label: Trade Finance Loan

loanTypeList.description: A list of credit facility types that are valid for those facilities described in the 'LoanDetails' element.

Amortising Home Loan.description: A loan that requires the borrower to make scheduled, periodic payments that are applied to both the principal and interest. An amortized loan payment first pays off the interest expense for the period; any remaining amount is put towards reducing the principal amount.
Amortising Home Loan.label: Amortising Home Loan

Bridging Finance.description: A short term loan designed to allow a borrower to finance the purchase of a new property before selling an existing property. An assessment for a bridging loan involves calculation of peak debt and end debt.
Bridging Finance.label: Bridging Finance

Chattel Mortgage.description: A finance company lends money to the customer to purchase movable equipment (the 'chattel'), in return for regular repayments. The customer takes ownership upon purchase, and an ASIC-registered Charge provides loan security. At term, the customer can either pay any residual value (gaining clear title via removal of the Charge), trade in the asset, or refinance the residual value.
Chattel Mortgage.label: Chattel Mortgage

Commercial Hire Purchase.description: The lessor secures and pays for an asset on the lessee's behalf with an offer to hire it back to the lessee for an agreed term. The lessor retains ownership of the asset until the lessee pays it off on a principal plus interest basis.
Commercial Hire Purchase.label: Commercial Hire Purchase

Credit Card.description: A type of unsecured revolving credit facility.
Credit Card.label: Credit Card

Finance Lease.description: An arrangement where a finance company purchases an asset, and use of the asset is granted to the customer through a series of payments until the end of term, when the customer can acquire ownership by paying the residual value.
Finance Lease.label: Finance Lease

Invoice Financing Loan.description: An invoice financing loan secured by one or more outstanding sales invoices owed to the borrower.
Invoice Financing Loan.label: Invoice Financing Loan

Lease.description: A type of rental arrangement other than Operating Lease or Finance Lease (which are each are listed separately).
Lease.label: Lease

Line of Credit.description: A revolving credit facility for a product that is not secured by residential property.
Line of Credit.label: Line of Credit

Line of Credit Home Loan.description: A revolving credit facility for a product that is secured by a residential property.
Line of Credit Home Loan.label: Line of Credit Home Loan

Mortgage Loan.description: This item is now deprecated and will be deleted in a future release. We suggest using either 'Amortising Home Loan' or 'Line of Credit Home Loan' instead. Mortgage Loan
Mortgage Loan.label: Mortgage Loan

Novated Lease.description: A finance agreement between a Financier/Lender, an individual that is usually the employee (Lessee) and their employer. This allows a lessee to lease a vehicle, and make repayments from their pre-tax salary through a salary sacrificing arrangement with their employer.
Novated Lease.label: Novated Lease

Operating Lease.description: An agreement where an asset's owner permits it's use by the customer for a term that is less than the useful or economic life of the asset in return for regular payments. Ownership rights are not transferred and the customer can return the equipment to the owner at the end of term without further obligation.
Operating Lease.label: Operating Lease

Reverse Mortgage.description: An equity release mortgage with accruing interest, repaid on the sale of the property.
Reverse Mortgage.label: Reverse Mortgage

Term Loan.description: A loan with a specified repayment period that is not secured by residential property.
Term Loan.label: Term Loan

Trade Finance Loan.description: A trade finance loan for financing domestic and international trade.
Trade Finance Loan.label: Trade Finance Loan

enum: Not Required to Lodge a Tax Return

Age Pension.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of an Age Pension.
Age Pension.label: Age Pension

Carer Payment.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of a Carer Payment.
Carer Payment.label: Carer Payment

Child Exemption.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments (other than shares in a public company) held by children under 16 years of age under certain specific conditions.
Child Exemption.label: Child Exemption

Disability Support Pension.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of a Disability Support Pension.
Disability Support Pension.label: Disability Support Pension

Non-Resident Exemption.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by residents living outside of Australia.
Non-Resident Exemption.label: Non-Resident Exemption

Not Required for Interest Income.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from interest bearing deposits and accounts with a financial institution, provided that the payment is less than $120 for the financial year (if the payment is not for the whole financial year, the $120 threshold is pro-rated).
Not Required for Interest Income.label: Not Required for Interest Income

Not Required to Lodge a Tax Return.description: An entity that isn't required to lodge an income tax return and doesn't have a TFN is taken to have quoted a TFN for an investment, which is reportable in an AIIR (Annual investment income report), to the investment body.
Not Required to Lodge a Tax Return.label: Not Required to Lodge a Tax Return
Not Required to Lodge a Tax Return.path: taxDeclarationExemptionCategoryList.Not Required to Lodge a Tax Return

Parenting Payment Single.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of a Parenting Payment Single.
Parenting Payment Single.label: Parenting Payment Single

Special Benefit.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of a Special Benefit.
Special Benefit.label: Special Benefit

Special Needs Pension.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of a Special Needs Pension.
Special Needs Pension.label: Special Needs Pension

Veteran Allowance.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of a Defence Force income support allowance from Veterans' Affairs
Veteran Allowance.label: Veteran Allowance

Veteran Pension.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of an age, invalidity or partner service pension from Veterans' Affairs.
Veteran Pension.label: Veteran Pension

Widow B Pension.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of a Widow B Pension.
Widow B Pension.label: Widow B Pension

Wife Pension.description: Investment bodies are not required to withhold amounts for non-quotation of a TFN or ABN from investments held by recipients of a Wife Pension.
Wife Pension.label: Wife Pension

Life Estate (Remainder Expectant for Less Than Entirety)

Bup / Gtp Title.description: Building Units Plan (BUP) / Group Titles Plan (GTP) Title
Bup / Gtp Title.label: Bup / Gtp Title

Community Title.description: Tenure held is under a Community Scheme or a Community Strata Scheme. Both divide land to create lots and common property in a similar manner to strata titles. Unlike a strata title, a scheme may include a development lot, retained by the developer, for later division into further lots within the scheme.
Community Title.label: Community Title

Company Title.description: Tenure is held by ownership of shares in a company that grant rights to exclusively occupy parts of land that the company owns.
Company Title.label: Company Title

Crown Land.description: Tenure held is in the 'right of the Crown' of either an individual State or the Commonwealth of Australia.
Crown Land.label: Crown Land

Crown Lease.description: Tenure held is under a Crown lease granted by the Crown over Crown land, commonly with a 99 year leasehold term.
Crown Lease.label: Crown Lease

Free and Unrestricted Right of Way.description: Free and Unrestricted Right of Way
Free and Unrestricted Right of Way.label: Free and Unrestricted Right of Way
Free and Unrestricted Right of Way.path: tenureTypeList.Free and Unrestricted Right of Way

Freehold.description: Tenure held is outright ownership, in perpetuity.
Freehold.label: Freehold

Group Titles Plan.description: Tenure held is as a lot collectively administered under the Group Titles Act 1980 (QLD).
Group Titles Plan.label: Group Titles Plan

Leasehold.description: Tenure held is as a lessee under a lease from the freehold owner of the property (lessor).
Leasehold.label: Leasehold

Life Estate (Remainder Expectant for Les.description: Life Estate (Remainder Expectant for Less Than Entirety)
Life Estate (Remainder Expectant for Les.label: Life Estate (Remainder Expectant for Less Than Entirety)
Life Estate (Remainder Expectant for Les.path: tenureTypeList.Life Estate (Remainder Expectant for Less Than Entirety)

Limited Torrens.description: Limited Torrens title is usually present due to a quick conversion from the Old Systems Title to Torrens Title. A limited certificate of title is issued by Land Registry Services indicating that the boundaries have not been examined in NSW LRS.
Limited Torrens.label: Limited Torrens

Miscellaneous Shack Leases.description: Miscellaneous Shack leases refer to the security built on crown land, or beach or river.
Miscellaneous Shack Leases.label: Miscellaneous Shack Leases

Moiety Title.description: Tenure held is a share of the whole of the land and a lease over a defined portion of the land for from the other owner or owners, typically covering maisonettes or attached cottages.
Moiety Title.label: Moiety Title

National Park (Atsi).description: National Park (Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander)
National Park (Atsi).label: National Park (Atsi)

None.description: Indicates that no tenure is specified.
None.label: None

Other Title.description: Indicates that the type of tenure held is not described by any of the other enumerated values.
Other Title.label: Other Title

Purple Title.description: Tenure held is ownership of an undivided share in a property, with the right to exclusively occupy certain areas in the complex determined by contract with each resident.
Purple Title.label: Purple Title

Strata Title.description: Tenure held is as a unit or lot on a plan of subdivision associated with townhouses, units and blocks of flats and based on the horizontal and vertical subdivision of air space. Owners have a certificate of title, are absolute owners of a freehold flat and have an undivided share of the common property.
Strata Title.label: Strata Title

Stratum Title.description: Tenure held is freehold over an apartment, unit or flat, with in addition the owner automatically becoming a member of a service company that administers, manages and maintains the property in which the owner's flat is registered.
Stratum Title.label: Stratum Title

Survey Strata Title.description: Equivalent to a Strata Title with the exception that no buildings are shown on the Plan.
Survey Strata Title.label: Survey Strata Title

Unit Title.description: Tenure held is unit title under the Unit Titles Act (ACT) which is the ACT equivalent of Strata Title.
Unit Title.label: Unit Title

Company.description: The title is granted by ownership of shares in a company that have rights to exclusively occupy parts of land that the company owns.
Company.label: Company

Old Law.description: The title is granted by a chain of title documents or deeds, the system replaced by Torrens Title.
Old Law.label: Old Law

Qualified.description: A folio in the Torrens Title Register in which is recorded a "caution" that has not been cancelled. A caution warns persons dealing with the registered proprietor that the land is held subject to any "subsisting interests" that may exist under Common Law or Old System.
Qualified.label: Qualified

Torrens.description: The title is registered in a public register that is maintained by a Land Registry under relevant legislation.
Torrens.label: Torrens

Unregistered.description: The title is pending registration in the Torrens Title Register.
Unregistered.label: Unregistered

Amortisation Term.description: The term specified is the amortisation term of the loan, being the period over which the amortising repayment is calculated.
Amortisation Term.label: Amortisation Term

Total Term.description: The term specified is the total term of the loan, being the period at the end of which the loan principal must be repaid.
Total Term.label: Total Term

Family Trust.description: A discretionary trust for which a family trust election has been made.
Family Trust.label: Family Trust

Protective.description: The trust has been established for a person who is unable to manage his or her own affairs.
Protective.label: Protective

Security Trust.description: A trust, typically a simple (bare) trust, set up to hold property as security for a loan, for example for an SMSF. Also known as a property trust.
Security Trust.label: Security Trust

Trading Trust.description: A trust that actively carries on business, and hence where the trust assets are used in the conduct of business.
Trading Trust.label: Trading Trust

trustRegulatorList.description: A list of the government authorities responsible for regulating the trust (for example, ATO, ASIC, or APRA).
trustRegulatorList.label: Trust Regulator List

Cash Management.description: A cash management trust is a trust that pools the relatively small investments of individuals and invests the funds it receives in short-dated securities (such as treasury notes and bank bills) that have traditionally required large minimum investments.
Cash Management.label: Cash Management

Discretionary.description: The trustee has discretion as to the distribution of trust property to the beneficiaries.
Discretionary.label: Discretionary

Fixed.description: The trustee holds the trust assets for the benefit of the beneficiaries in specified fixed proportions.
Fixed.label: Fixed

Hybrid.description: A trust that combines elements of both fixed and discretionary trusts, in that the trustee must pay a certain amount of the trust property to each beneficiary, but otherwise has discretion as to how any remaining trust property is distributed.
Hybrid.label: Hybrid

Simple.description: A trust with one trustee and one beneficiary, and where the trustee has no active duty beyond conveying the property to the beneficiary at some future time determined by the trust. Also known as a bare trust.
Simple.label: Simple

Superannuation Fund.description: A superannuation fund is a form of trust designed to provide retirement or death benefits for its members, with those members being the beneficiaries.
Superannuation Fund.label: Superannuation Fund

Unit.description: The beneficiaries (called unit holders) each possess a certain share (called units) and can direct the trustee to pay money to them out of the trust property according to the number of units they possess.
Unit.label: Unit

typeOfIncorporationList.description: A list of valid types of incorporation that describe the valid company structures.

Inc.description: An incorporated association under the relevant state or territory legislation.
Inc.label: Inc

Ltd.description: A public company limited by shares.
Ltd.label: Ltd

NL.description: A "No Liability Company", meaning that it must be solely for the objective of mining and have no further call on any of its unpaid shares.
NL.label: NL

Owners Corporation.description: A legal entity formed by a group of individuals or entities for a specific purpose, typically involving collective ownership, management, or administration. It has rights and duties under the law, similar to those of an individual person. This structure provides the company with a distinct legal identity that is completely separate from its owners or members.
Owners Corporation.label: Owners Corporation

Pty.description: A proprietary company where the shareholders are liable for the debts of the company.
Pty.label: Pty

Pty Ltd.description: A Proprietary Limited company, being a private company limited by shares.
Pty Ltd.label: Pty Ltd

typeOfIncorporationList.label: Type Of Incorporation List

uniqueIDType.description: Value must be unique within the scope, e.g. Application, Valuation, LMI response, etc.
uniqueIDType.label: Unique ID Type

urlPattern.description: The uniform resource locator, is a specific character string that constitutes a reference to a resource. In most web browsers, the URL of a web page is displayed on top inside an address bar.
urlPattern.label: URL Pattern

AVM.description: An AVM (Automated Valuation Model) requires no input from a qualified valuer, but instead use computer models based on attribute data and recent comparable sales data to estimate a value.
AVM.label: AVM

Costing.description: A Costing is an evaluation of a construction contract to determine if the contract price is appropriate for the building being constructed, and to estimate the market value as if complete. Used for off the plan or To Be Erected (TBE) property.
Costing.label: Costing

Desktop.description: A Desktop Valuation requires no internal or external inspection, instead qualified valuers use data about the property (attributes, photos, and comparable sales) to value a property.
Desktop.label: Desktop

Full Registered.description: A Full Registered Valuation requires an internal and external inspection of the property by a qualified valuer.
Full Registered.label: Full Registered

Kerb Side.description: A Kerb Side Valuation requires an external sighting of the property from the street by a qualified valuer.
Kerb Side.label: Kerb Side

Progress Inspection.description: A Progress Inspection is an inspection and valuation of a building under construction.
Progress Inspection.label: Progress Inspection

Add Guarantee Security.description: Add a security to an existing guarantee.
Add Guarantee Security.label: Add Guarantee Security

Release Guarantee Security.description: Release a security from an existing guarantee.
Release Guarantee Security.label: Release Guarantee Security

Substitute Guarantee Security.description: Substitute one security for another under an existing guarantee.
Substitute Guarantee Security.label: Substitute Guarantee Security

@GSTComponent.description: Dollar amount of the GST component.

Builder.description: The contact for arranging the inspection of the property is the builder.

Property Agent.description: The contact for arranging inspection of the property is the real estate agent acting for the vendor of the property. Applicable when the property is being purchased by the applicant.

Tenant.description: The contact for arranging inspection of the property is the tenant that resides in the property. Applicable when the property is leased.

Vendor.description: The contact for arranging inspection of the property is the seller.

description: This schema (LIXI-DAS-2_2_92-Annotated.xsd) is a sub-schema derived from the LIXI Master Schema (LIXI-Master-2_2_94-Annotated.xsd) that includes the annotation documentation.

Package.description: The root element that contains a message for exchange between two end-points involved in the workflow related to the processing of an application for a new financial product or change management of an existing financial product. The message contains instructions to the recipient requesting some workflow activity along with data related to: the applicant and the financial product involved; the publisher; one or more recipients; schema version information; and any related attachments.
Package.label: Package

@ProductionData.description: Indicates whether this file contains production or test data.
@ProductionData.label: Production Data

Attachment.description: Contains information about a document that is attached to the application, either by being embedded or by reference to a URL, or both.

@DocumentManagementSystem.description: The name or the internal code for the Document Management System in which the attachment described by the URI is stored.
@DocumentManagementSystem.label: Document Management System

@Filename.description: For each attachment, the name for the attached file, including filename extension may be provided
@Filename.label: Filename

@MediaType.description: Media type of the Base64 attachment e.g. "image/png" or "application/pdf".
@MediaType.label: Media Type

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this document that is attached to the application. The sequence number is a one-based field.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@URI.description: For each attachment, the URI that identifies where the attached file might be accessed from. While it is anticipated that it will generally be of the form "http://" or "ftp://", there is no requirement for this to be the case.
@URI.label: URI

Content.description: The details of a document that is included in the attachment.

@Description.description: A description of the type of document attached. To be used when the type is 'Other'.
@Description.label: Description

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this content within the sequence. The sequence number is a one-based field.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@Type.description: The type of document included in the attachment.
@Type.label: Type

Content.label: Content

InlineAttachment.description: For each attachment, the document itself can be embedded in the XML in a text encoded format.
InlineAttachment.label: Inline Attachment

Attachment.label: Attachment

Application.description: The set of borrower- and broker-provided data for a single loan application.

@ProductionData.description: Indicates whether this file contains production or test data.
@ProductionData.label: Production Data
