If there is an assignment certificate, the details of the certificate are captured here.
@AssignmentCertificate.label: Assignment Certificate

@EntitlementCertificate.description: Under the Defence Services Housing loan program, a certificate of entitlement certifies that a subsidy is payable by the Commonwealth to the credit provider if, in accordance with the agreement, the credit provider makes that advance to the applicant or the assignee of the applicant. If there is an entitlement certificate, details of the certificate must be provided.
@EntitlementCertificate.label: Entitlement Certificate

@FileNumber.description: Under the Defence Services Housing loan program, the Commonwealth's file number for the qualifying applicant.
@FileNumber.label: File Number

@Subsidised.description: Indicates that the DSH loan being applied for is subsidised
@Subsidised.label: Subsidised

@Supplement.description: Indicates that the DSH loan being applied for is a supplement to an existing DSH loan, whereby additional available DSH loan funds are advanced to the applicant.
@Supplement.label: Supplement

DiscountMargin.description: Contains information about a discount in relation to the loan facility that the applicant claims they are entitled to. The discount claimed may be in the form of either a rate reduction margin or a dollar amount. The discount claimed is different from, and therefore may be in addition to, a general special offer that applies to all applicants, or discount that is available under a product package.

@DiscountRate.description: Captures the percentage rate discount the applicant claims they qualify for or are entitled to. If the discount is for 0.6% off the variable rate which is 6.5%, the value to be entered in this field should be '0.6'. If the borrower gets 0.5 in addition to 0.2, then the net Discount Rate will be 0.7
@DiscountRate.label: Discount Rate

@DiscountReason.description: Captures an explanation of why the applicant qualifies for or is entitled to the discount claimed.
@DiscountReason.label: Discount Reason

@DiscountedAmount.description: Captures the dollar amount of the discount the applicant claims they qualify for or are entitled to. The dollar amount is to be deducted from the calculated periodic repayment.
@DiscountedAmount.label: Discounted Amount

@Duration.description: The duration over which the discount is to be applied
@Duration.label: Duration

@DurationUnits.description: The units of time of the specified duration
@DurationUnits.label: Duration Units

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this discount margin within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

DiscountMargin.label: Discount Margin

DocumentationInstructions.description: Contains information specifying where the lender is to send the loan documents once the loan has been approved. This nomination over-rides an equivalent one at the Application level.
DocumentationInstructions.label: Documentation Instructions

EquityRelease.description: Contains information about the loan amount requested that applies only when the loan product being applied for is a reverse mortgage, or equity release.
EquityRelease.label: Equity Release

@ProtectedEquity.description: An applicant for a reverse mortgage may specify that a percentage of the equity in the security property be protected against the increasing balance of the loan, to preserve it for the borrower's future needs. The lender cannot use proceeds of sale of the property that relate to the protected equity portion of the loan to repay the outstanding balance of the loan.
@ProtectedEquity.label: Protected Equity

@ProtectedEquityPercentage.description: If a percentage of the applicant's equity in the security property is to be protected, specifies the percentage of equity protected.
@ProtectedEquityPercentage.label: Protected Equity Percentage

AccommodationBond.description: Captures information about the bond that the applicant intends to deposit with an aged-care facility when they taking up residence.
AccommodationBond.label: Accommodation Bond

@ExpectedAdmissionDate.description: For an accommodation bond, the expected date that the aged person will take up residence in the aged care facility must be provided.
@ExpectedAdmissionDate.label: Expected Admission Date

@ServiceProviderName.description: For an accommodation bond, the name of the aged care facility that will receive the accommodation bond must be provided - the "aged care facility name";
@ServiceProviderName.label: Service Provider Name

@ServiceProviderNumber.description: For an accommodation bond, the service provider number of the aged care facility, probably the unique RACS ID (Residential Aged Care Service) allocated by the Department of Health and Ageing must be provided
@ServiceProviderNumber.label: Service Provider Number

Amount.description: For a reverse mortgage, contains information about the way that the applicant wants the loan funds to be advanced. The loan amount requested may be advanced in combinations of the following: 1. a lump sum paid at settlement; 2. instalment amounts paid periodically; and/or 3) a cash reserve amount that may be drawn down at will.
Amount.label: Amount

@CalculateAsPercentage.description: For a reverse mortgage, captures the percentage of the value of the security property that the applicant requests to borrow. This is provided as an as an alternative to specifying an absolute loan amount. The actual loan amount will be calculated once the valuation of the security property has been completed.
@CalculateAsPercentage.label: Calculate As Percentage

@CashReserve.description: Captures the amount of the total loan amount requested that is to be advanced to the applicant as a cash reserve. Also known as a line of credit.
@CashReserve.label: Cash Reserve

@InstalmentsAmount.description: Captures the amount of the total loan amount requested that is to be advanced to the applicant in instalments. This amount is the sum of the instalment payments.
@InstalmentsAmount.label: Instalments Amount

@LumpSum.description: Captures the amount of the total loan amount requested that is to be advanced to the applicant as a lump sum at settlement.
@LumpSum.label: Lump Sum

@VaryOnValuation.description: The amount of the loan advanced may vary if the amount the security property is valued at differs from the applicant's estimate of its value. The applicant may be able to specify what component of the payment should be varied in this situation. The applicant may specify that one of the lump sum amount OR the cash reserve amount OR the periodic payment be varied by any shortfall or surplus when the valuation amount differs from the applicant's estimate.
@VaryOnValuation.label: Vary On Valuation

Instalments.description: Contains information about instalment payments, including the amount, number and regularity, and start date for the payments.
Instalments.label: Instalments

@AmountPerInstalment.description: For instalment payments with a specified amount, the amount of the monthly (or other period ) payments must be provided.
@AmountPerInstalment.label: Amount Per Instalment

@IndexRate.description: If instalment payments are to be indexed, specifies the percentage rate of indexation to be applied.
@IndexRate.label: Index Rate

@Indexed.description: The applicant may elect to have their instalment payments indexed in order to adjust for inflation. The applicant must be able to specify if their instalment payments are to be indexed, and if so the rate of indexation to be applied.
@Indexed.label: Indexed

@NumberOfInstalments.description: For instalment payments without a specified amount, the number of instalment payments to be made must be provided
@NumberOfInstalments.label: Number Of Instalments

Favouree.description: The beneficiary for the bank guarantee.
Favouree.label: Favouree

@x_Favouree.description: A cross-reference to the party that is listed as the beneficiary for the bank guarantee.
@x_Favouree.label: Favouree

FeaturesSelected.description: Contains information about the product features requested by the applicant.
FeaturesSelected.label: Features Selected

@ChequeBook.description: Indicates whether the applicant requests that a cheque book be issued for the loan account.
@ChequeBook.label: Cheque Book

@CreditCard.description: Indicates whether the applicant has requested a credit card.
@CreditCard.label: Credit Card

@DebitCard.description: Indicates whether the applicant has requested a debit card.
@DebitCard.label: Debit Card

@DepositBook.description: Indicates whether the applicant has requested a deposit book
@DepositBook.label: Deposit Book

@HolidayLeave.description: Indicates whether the applicant requests that the loan product allows them to temporarily pause making repayments while they are not earning a regular income or for some other acceptable reason.
@HolidayLeave.label: Holiday Leave

@Offset.description: Indicates whether the applicant requests that a 100% offset account facility be established for the loan account.
@Offset.label: Offset

@OffsetPercentage.description: The percentage of the balance in the offset account that should be used to reduce the outstanding balance on the loan account when calculating interest payable. Typically 100%, but some lenders offer partial offset accounts.
@OffsetPercentage.label: Offset Percentage

@ParentalLeave.description: Indicates whether the applicant requests that the loan product allows them to reduce their repayments while they are not earning a regular income because they are taking maternity/parental leave.
@ParentalLeave.label: Parental Leave

@PartialOffset.description: Indicates whether the applicant requests that an offset account be established for the loan account with less than 100% offset of the balance in the offset account against the outstanding loan balance.
@PartialOffset.label: Partial Offset

@Portability.description: Indicates whether the applicant requests that the loan facility be portable between security properties.
@Portability.label: Portability

@ProgressiveDraw.description: Indicates whether the applicant requests that the loan funds be drawn down progressively, typically against progress of stages under a construction contract.
@ProgressiveDraw.label: Progressive Draw

@RateLock.description: Indicates whether the applicant requests that the interest rate for a fixed rate product be 'locked' until settlement
@RateLock.label: Rate Lock

@Redraw.description: Indicates whether the applicant requests that the loan product permit the redraw of loan principal that has been repaid in advance of the amortisation schedule for the loan.
@Redraw.label: Redraw

@SplitLoan.description: Indicates that the applicant requests that the loan amount be split between two or more separate accounts or split facilities.
@SplitLoan.label: Split Loan

ExtraFeature.description: Information about a product feature that is requested on the loan account.

@Description.description: Specific information, value or enumeration related to the specific feature (name).
@Description.label: Description

@Name.description: The name of the specific feature being requested. Free text field although lenders may provide enumerations
@Name.label: Name

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this extra feature within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

ExtraFeature.label: Extra Feature

OffsetAccount.description: Identifies the BSB, Account Number and Account Name for the offset account.

@IsExisting.description: Indicates whether the Offset Account detailed is an existing Offset Account or not
@IsExisting.label: Is Existing

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this offset account within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@x_Account.description: A cross reference to an account (a Non Real Estate Asset element) to be used as the offset account.
@x_Account.label: Account

AccountNumber.description: Account number details such as BSB, Account Number and Account Name for the offset account
AccountNumber.label: Account Number

OffsetAccount.label: Offset Account

FundsDisbursement.description: Specification of how funds are to be distributed.
FundsDisbursement.label: Funds Disbursement

Guarantor.description: A reference to the party that is applying to be a guarantor on this loan account.

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this guarantor within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@x_Guarantor.description: A reference to the party that is applying to be a guarantor on this loan account.
@x_Guarantor.label: Guarantor

Guarantor.label: Guarantor

InterestPayable.description: Interest that will be paid over the term of the loan.
InterestPayable.label: Interest Payable

@TotalAmount.description: The total interest amount that will be paid over the term of the loan.
@TotalAmount.label: Total Amount

LendingPurpose.description: Details of the purpose for which the applicant intends to use the loan funds.

@ABSLendingPurpose.description: Captures the free text description of the ABS Lending Purpose Code.
@ABSLendingPurpose.label: ABS Lending Purpose

@ABSLendingPurposeCode.description: Captures the ABS code for this purpose for which the loan funds will be used by the applicant.
@ABSLendingPurposeCode.label: ABS Lending Purpose Code

@Description.description: Captures a description of the purpose if none of the purposes specified in the lender's enumerated list of purposes adequately described the true purpose.
@Description.label: Description

@IncludesRefinancing.description: Whether all or part of this credit facility will be used to refinance in full or in part one or many existing credit facilities.
@IncludesRefinancing.label: Includes Refinancing

@InternalRefinance.description: This loan is associated with an internal refinance.
@InternalRefinance.label: Internal Refinance

@LenderCode.description: Captures the lender-specified code for this purpose for which the loan funds will be used by the applicant.
@LenderCode.label: Lender Code

@NonRefinancingLendingReason.description: The principal reason for lending when the loan is not to be used to refinance liabilities.
@NonRefinancingLendingReason.label: Non Refinancing Lending Reason

@PurposeAmount.description: The amount of the loan funds that will be used for the specified purpose.
@PurposeAmount.label: Purpose Amount

@RefinancingReason.description: Borrowers should inform the lender of the reason for refinancing liabilities
@RefinancingReason.label: Refinancing Reason

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this lending purpose within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

LendingPurpose.label: Lending Purpose

LoanPurpose.description: Contains information about the main purpose for which the applicant intends to use the loan funds.
LoanPurpose.label: Loan Purpose

@NCCPStatus.description: Captures whether the loan is regulated by the NCCP. This determination is made by the lender based on information provided by the applicant about the purpose for which the loan funds will be used, so this field is unlikely to be requested from the applicant.
@NCCPStatus.label: NCCP Status

@Occupancy.description: The applicant's intention as to who will occupy the dwelling after the purchase completes.
@Occupancy.label: Occupancy

@OwnerBuilderApplication.description: Indicates whether the applicant intends to use the loan funds to fund the building of an owner/builder constructed property.
@OwnerBuilderApplication.label: Owner Builder Application

@PrimaryPurpose.description: Captures the primary purpose for which the loan funds will be used by the applicant. Categories reflect the categories used in classifying a loan as regulated or unregulated under the NCCP.
@PrimaryPurpose.label: Primary Purpose

Package.description: Contains information about a package option that may be available for the individual loan account.

@Category.description: Captures a lender defined category to which the requested package belongs.
@Category.label: Category

@Code.description: A unique code representing the product package being requested by the applicant.
@Code.label: Code

@MemberID.description: Membership Identifier of the applicant issued by the Organisation the applicant claims to belong to and therefore qualify for the package associated with that Organisation. May be provided when Organisation is specified.
@MemberID.label: Member ID

@Name.description: Captures the name of a package that the applicant is applying for. A package commonly gives the borrowers certain benefits, such as an interest rate and fee discounts, for a fee. There may be rules that determine whether the applicants qualify for the package.
@Name.label: Name

@OptionCode.description: A unique code identifying an option that applies to a package.
@OptionCode.label: Option Code

@Organisation.description: A code or name that identifies the organisation under which the package is offered.
@Organisation.label: Organisation

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this package within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

Package.label: Package

ProposedRepayment.description: Contains information that specifies how the borrower(s) intend to make regular or structured repayments.
ProposedRepayment.label: Proposed Repayment

@AnniversaryDate.description: The preferred start (anniversary) date for regular repayments
@AnniversaryDate.label: Anniversary Date

@Description.description: A description of the repayment method that will be used to repay the loan when Method = "Other"
@Description.label: Description

@Method.description: The payment method that will be used to effect the transfer of repayments on the loan to the lender. Examples include salary sacrifice, direct debit and BPAY.
@Method.label: Method

@PaymentTiming.description: Indicates the timing of payments with respect to their payment period.
@PaymentTiming.label: Payment Timing

@PerDiemPaymentAmount.description: An optional partial-period payment to bring payment periods for several loans onto a common anniversary date (this is a total amount, so it includes GST and Stamp Duty).
@PerDiemPaymentAmount.label: Per Diem Payment Amount

@PerDiemPaymentDate.description: The proposed date of the per diem payment
@PerDiemPaymentDate.label: Per Diem Payment Date

@PerDiemPaymentGSTAmount.description: The dollar amount of the GST portion of within the Per Diem Payment Amount
@PerDiemPaymentGSTAmount.label: Per Diem Payment GST Amount

@PerDiemPaymentStampDutyAmount.description: The dollar amount of the Stamp Duty portion of the Per Diem Payment Amount
@PerDiemPaymentStampDutyAmount.label: Per Diem Payment Stamp Duty Amount

@Regular.description: Flag to indicate whether payments are regular (same amount on regular intervals) or structured (irregular intervals and/or amounts)
@Regular.label: Regular

CreditCard.description: Details of the credit card to be used for repayments
CreditCard.label: Credit Card

@CardHolderName.description: Cardholder name on the credit card to be used for repayments
@CardHolderName.label: Card Holder Name

@ExpiryMonth.description: Month of expiry date of the credit card to be used for repayments
@ExpiryMonth.label: Expiry Month

@ExpiryYear.description: Year of expiry date of the credit card to be used for repayments
@ExpiryYear.label: Expiry Year

@Number.description: Credit card number to be used for repayments
@Number.label: Number

@Type.description: Type of credit card to be used for repayments
@Type.label: Type

FromAccount.description: Captures BSB, Account Number and Account Name for the account from which the repayments will be made.
FromAccount.label: From Account

RegularRepayment.description: Container element for information associated with regular repayments

@Amount.description: Preferred or nominated total regular repayment amount (incorporating any GST or Stamp Duty in the case of Equipment Finance Transactions)
@Amount.label: Amount

@DayOfMonth.description: The day of the month that the regular repayment will be made.
@DayOfMonth.label: Day Of Month

@DayOfWeek.description: The day of the week that the regular repayment will be made.
@DayOfWeek.label: Day Of Week

@EndOfPeriod.description: The payment will be made at the end of the end of the period e.g. end of month (EOM), end of quarter (EOQ), or end of year (EOY).
@EndOfPeriod.label: End Of Period

@Frequency.description: Captures the applicants' preferred period for making loan repayments for the loan account. Captured when the loan product selected offers a range of repayment periods, enabling the applicant to nominate a period which best suits their needs in terms of income and the desire to reduce interest over the life of the loan by accelerating the reduction of the principal balance.
@Frequency.label: Frequency

@FrequencyInterval.description: The time interval at which the repayment is repeated. Expressed as a multiple of the specified frequency.
@FrequencyInterval.label: Frequency Interval

@GSTAmount.description: The dollar amount of the GST incorporated into the Regular Payment (typically used in Equipment Finance Transactions).
@GSTAmount.label: GST Amount

@InterestPayment.description: This payment covers the interest amount.
@InterestPayment.label: Interest Payment

@LastRepaymentDate.description: The date that the last repayment of this regular repayment will occur.
@LastRepaymentDate.label: Last Repayment Date

@LoanPaymentScheduleType.description: The type of loan payment schedule.
@LoanPaymentScheduleType.label: Loan Payment Schedule Type

@PrincipalPayment.description: This payment reduces the principal amount.
@PrincipalPayment.label: Principal Payment

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this regular repayment within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@StampDutyAmount.description: The dollar amount of the Stamp Duty incorporated into the Regular Payment (typically used in Equipment Finance Transactions).
@StampDutyAmount.label: Stamp Duty Amount

@TotalRepayments.description: Captures the total number of loan repayments.
@TotalRepayments.label: Total Repayments

@Week.description: The week within the period that the regular repayment will be made.
@Week.label: Week

RegularRepayment.label: Regular Repayment

StructuredPayments.description: Container element used when structured repayments rather than regular repayments are proposed or advised
StructuredPayments.label: Structured Payments

@BaseFrequency.description: Although structured payments may have arbitrary payment dates, the base frequency defines the fundamental unit of time used for determining payment dates and interest payment calculations.
@BaseFrequency.label: Base Frequency

Payment.description: Details of itemised proposed payments. A given loan may have differing payment regimes at different periods in its total term (e.g. a fixed rate IO loan may have an initial Fixed Rate IO period, followed by a Variable Rate Interest Only period, followed by a Variable Rate Principal and Interest period.)

@Amount.description: Captures the total amount of the payment in the payment period, being the calculated repayment amount plus any service fee, GST or Stamp Duty.
@Amount.label: Amount

@Date.description: The date of the specified payment
@Date.label: Date

@GSTAmount.description: The dollar amount of the GST incorporated into this Structured Payment (typically used in Equipment Finance Transactions).
@GSTAmount.label: GST Amount

@GSTOnTermChargesIncluded.description: The GST on term charges is included in this payment. The GST amount for this payment includes both the GST charged on this payment amount, and the GST on term charges for the full term of the loan.
@GSTOnTermChargesIncluded.label: GST On Term Charges Included

@GSTRebateAmount.description: An input tax credit (ITC) amount that the applicant can claim on an eligible purchase.
@GSTRebateAmount.label: GST Rebate Amount

@GSTRebateAmountReplacingPayment.description: The payment will only consist of the GST rebate amount.
@GSTRebateAmountReplacingPayment.label: GST Rebate Amount Replacing Payment

@SequenceNumber.description: Captures the sequence number of the payment or payment period.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@StampDutyAmount.description: The dollar amount of the Stamp Duty incorporated into this Structured Payment (typically used in Equipment Finance Transactions).
@StampDutyAmount.label: Stamp Duty Amount

Payment.label: Payment

RateComposition.description: The structure of the interest rate to the borrower, based on the delivery rate with applied margins

@CustomerRiskMargin.description: The customer risk margin added (as a percentage) based on the risk the customer presents to the bank.
@CustomerRiskMargin.label: Customer Risk Margin

@DisclosedToCustomer.description: The details of the rate are disclosed to the customer.
@DisclosedToCustomer.label: Disclosed To Customer

@IntroductoryMargin.description: The introductory margin added (as a percentage) during the introductory period or honeymoon period.
@IntroductoryMargin.label: Introductory Margin

@PaymentTypeMargin.description: The payment type margin added (as a percentage) based on the payment type.
@PaymentTypeMargin.label: Payment Type Margin

@PricingConstruct.description: The pricing construct used to calculate the rate i.e. Base Rate + Term Premium.
@PricingConstruct.label: Pricing Construct

@ProductMargin.description: The product margin added (as a percentage) based on the specific product type.
@ProductMargin.label: Product Margin

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this rate composition within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@SubsidyRateSacrifice.description: Rate added to the borrower rate
@SubsidyRateSacrifice.label: Subsidy Rate Sacrifice

@TermPremium.description: The term premium added (as a percentage) based on the loan term.
@TermPremium.label: Term Premium

@TotalInterestRate.description: The total interest rate for this rate composition scheme.
@TotalInterestRate.label: Total Interest Rate

BaseRate.description: The base rate on which other rates are calculated.
BaseRate.label: Base Rate

@Name.description: The base rate name.
@Name.label: Name

@Rate.description: The base rate as a percentage.
@Rate.label: Rate

RateComposition.label: Rate Composition

RateLock.description: A rate lock applied to the proposed annual interest rate for this loan. The fixed interest rate for this loan will not be subect to market rate fluctuations for the specified period.
RateLock.label: Rate Lock

@ExpiryDate.description: The date when the rate lock expires.
@ExpiryDate.label: Expiry Date

@StartDate.description: The date when the rate lock begins.
@StartDate.label: Start Date

Duration.description: The duration for which the rate is locked in.
Duration.label: Duration

Security.description: Contains a reference to a security property that is submitted with the loan application, and information about the relationship between the subject loan account and that security property.

@Description.description: The description of the security offered for this loan.
@Description.label: Description

@NumericPriority.description: The numeric representation of the priority of the security offered for this loan.
@NumericPriority.label: Numeric Priority

@Priority.description: The priority of the new mortgage that is offered as security for the loans being applied for. When the mortgage is already held by the lender being applied to, this is the priority of that existing mortgage.
@Priority.label: Priority

@PriorityAmount.description: The maximum dollar amount available to be recovered.
@PriorityAmount.label: Priority Amount

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this security within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@x_Security.description: Contains a reference to a security (real estate or non real estate asset) that is submitted with the loan application, and information about the relationship between the subject loan account and that security.
@x_Security.label: Security

InFavourOf.description: The party to whom the security is in favour.

@Name.description: The name of the party to whom the security is in favour.
@Name.label: Name

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this party within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

InFavourOf.label: In Favour Of

RelatedParty.description: The link to the related parties for the security.

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this related party within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@TypeOfRelationship.description: The type of relationship to the related party.
@TypeOfRelationship.label: Type Of Relationship

@x_Party.description: The cross-reference to the related party.
@x_Party.label: Party

RelatedParty.label: Related Party

SecurityAgreement.description: Security agreement details for this security.
SecurityAgreement.label: Security Agreement

Security.label: Security

Software.description: The software application used by the loan originator.
Software.label: Software

@Description.description: A description of the software provider, for example the company name.
@Description.label: Description

@Name.description: The name of the software application used by the loan originator.
@Name.label: Name

SupplementaryCardholder.description: Contains a link to a supplementary (non liable) cardholder.

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this supplementary cardholder within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@x_SupplementaryCardholder.description: Link to the loan party, related party or household dependant that will be a supplementary (non liable) cardholder.
@x_SupplementaryCardholder.label: Supplementary Cardholder

SupplementaryCardholder.label: Supplementary Cardholder

Term.description: Details of the total term of the credit product and any introductory terms, such as an interest only term (including interest only reasons) or a fixed rate term that applies for an initial period at the start of the product.
Term.label: Term

@GSTOnTermCharges.description: The GST component of the term charges amount.
@GSTOnTermCharges.label: GST On Term Charges

@GSTOnTermChargesCapitalised.description: The GST component of the term charges will be added to the total amount financed for the loan.
@GSTOnTermChargesCapitalised.label: GST On Term Charges Capitalised

@InterestType.description: Captures the type of interest that is to be paid during the specified term.
@InterestType.label: Interest Type

@InterestTypeDuration.description: The duration of the fixed interest rate period, as a whole number multiple of the Units.
@InterestTypeDuration.label: Interest Type Duration

@InterestTypeUnits.description: The units of time that are used to define the duration of the fixed interest rate period.
@InterestTypeUnits.label: Interest Type Units

@OngoingTerm.description: There is no fixed end date for the term of the loan. The life of the loan will continue indefinitely until the loan is closed or terminated.
@OngoingTerm.label: Ongoing Term

@PaymentType.description: Captures the type of repayment that is to be made during the specified term
@PaymentType.label: Payment Type

@PaymentTypeDuration.description: The duration of the interest only period, as a whole number multiple of the Units.
@PaymentTypeDuration.label: Payment Type Duration

@PaymentTypeUnits.description: The units of time that are used to define the duration of the interest only period.
@PaymentTypeUnits.label: Payment Type Units

@TermChargesAmount.description: The dollar amount of the term charges over the full term of the loan. Term charges are the total interest amount charged, plus any undisclosed capitalised fees, plus brokerage fees.
@TermChargesAmount.label: Term Charges Amount

@TotalFeesAmount.description: The anticipated total dollar amount of all fees paid over the full term of the loan.
@TotalFeesAmount.label: Total Fees Amount

@TotalInterestAmount.description: The anticipated total dollar amount of interest paid over the full term of the loan.
@TotalInterestAmount.label: Total Interest Amount

@TotalRepayments.description: The anticipated total number of repayments over the full term of the loan.
@TotalRepayments.label: Total Repayments

@TotalRepaymentsAmount.description: The anticipated total dollar amount of all repayments including interest paid over the full term of the loan.
@TotalRepaymentsAmount.label: Total Repayments Amount

@TotalTermDuration.description: The Duration of the specified loan term, as a multiple of the Units
@TotalTermDuration.label: Total Term Duration

@TotalTermType.description: The type of loan term should indicate that the loan term is either the total length of the term or the amortised term as required by the lender.
@TotalTermType.label: Total Term Type

@TotalTermUnits.description: Captures the period described by the number specified for term.
@TotalTermUnits.label: Total Term Units

DistinctLoanPeriod.description: A distinct loan period, where each period may have a different payment type, interest type, rate composition.

@EndDate.description: The end date of the distinct loan period.
@EndDate.label: End Date

@InterestType.description: The type of interest that is to be paid during the distinct loan period.
@InterestType.label: Interest Type

@PaymentType.description: The type of repayment that is to be made during the distinct loan period.
@PaymentType.label: Payment Type

@SequenceNumber.description: The order of this distinct loan period within the sequence.
@SequenceNumber.label: Sequence Number

@StartDate.description: The start date of the distinct loan period.
@StartDate.label: Start Date

@TotalFeesAmount.description: The anticipated total dollar amount of all fees paid during this distinct loan period.
@TotalFeesAmount.label: Total Fees Amount

@TotalInterestAmount.description: The anticipated total dollar amount of interest paid during this distinct loan period.

Publisher.description: The publisher of the specific XML file, being the party responsible for the content of the file as well as the work instruction, and to whom the response message would be delivered. For a mortgage broker sending an application to a lender, this would likely be the aggregator if they are providing the software, or perhaps the broker company or broker otherwise. For a lender requesting LMI, the lender is the publisher. For the LMI response, the LMI provider is the publisher.

@LIXICustomVersion.description: Each LIXI Schema that is customised by restriction is allocated a Custom Version Identifier. If the XML instance is created from a LIXI Transaction Schema the LIXICustomVersion is optional and should remain empty. If the XML instance is created from a schema that has been Customised by Restriction, this attribute is mandatory and holds the composite identifier constructed from: the LIXI Code of the author organisation; the Customisation Code (jointly defined by LIXI and the customisation author); and the datetimestamp of when the Customised Schema was created.
